t the 2010 Commonwealth Games|Swimming]]||175\n|-\n|align=center| 70 || {{flagCGFteam|ZAM|2010}} || {{sortname|Rachel|Nachula}} || [[Athletics at the 2010 Commonwealth Games|Athletics]]||22\n|-\n|align=center| 71 || {{flagCGFteam|IND|2010}} || {{sortname|Abhinav|Bindra}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/news/bindra-to-be-the-flag-bearer-confusion-over-torch-bearers-names-news-national-kkbtOfahchi.html |title=Bindra to be the flag bearer, confusion over torch bearers names |publisher=Sify.com |date=1 October 2010 |accessdate=14 October 2010}}</ref> || [[Shooting at the 2010 Commonwealth Games|Shooting]]||495\n|}\n* Pakistan's flag bearer was scheduled to be weightlifter [[Shujha-ud-din Malik]]. However, chef de mission Muhammad Ali Shah announced that he would carry the flag and took it from the designated flag-bearer.<ref>[http://www.thenews.com.pk/latest-news/2295.htm \"Pak CWG contingent hit by controversy\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101006104429/http://www.thenews.com.pk/latest-news/2295.htm |date=6 October 2010 }}, ''The News'', 3 October 2010</ref>\n\n==Spectators' response==\n\nIn the opening ceremony the head of organizing committee faced embarrassment, when he was booed by the spectators at the start of his welcome speech to 60,000 spectators in the opening ceremony. The atmosphere otherwise for the teams and officials was fine, especially when they offered warm applause to the neighbouring Pakistan squad, with whom it has tense relationships. Sri Lanka also got a loud applause. The head finished his speech in five minutes and then handed over to Michael Fennell, the Chief of the Commonwealth Games Federation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/wps/wcm/connect/dawn-content-library/dawn/news/sport/games-spectators-boo-delhi-chief-organiser-at-opening-ceremony-jd-03 |title=Sport &#124; Spectators boo chief organiser at opening ceremony |publisher=Dawn.Com |date=3 October 2010 |accessdate=14 October 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101014012850/http://www.dawn.com/wps/wcm/connect/dawn-content-library/dawn/news/sport/games-spectators-boo-delhi-chief-organiser-at-opening-ceremony-jd-03 |archivedate=14 October 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Baton Procession==\nBoxer [[Vijender Singh]] carried the [[Queen's Baton]] into the [[Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium, Delhi|Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium]], at the Opening Ceremony.<ref name=CBC-Baton/><ref name=Geetika>[http://blog.livemint.com/news/2010/10/cwg-opening-ceremony-live-blog/ \"CWG Opening ceremony: Live Blog\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101004165924/http://blog.livemint.com/news/2010/10/cwg-opening-ceremony-live-blog/ |date=4 October 2010 }}, '''Geetika Rustagi''', ''3 October 2010'' . Retrieved 5 October 2010.</ref> The baton was then passed to boxer [[Mary Kom]], 5-time world champion.<ref name=CBC-Baton/><ref name=Geetika/> It was then passed to [[Samresh Jung]], who was named best competitor of the [[2006 Commonwealth Games]] in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]] .<ref name=CBC-Baton/><ref name=Geetika/> It was then passed to [[Sushil Kumar (wrestler)|Sushil Kumar]], world champion wrestler,<ref name=CBC-Baton/><ref name=Geetika/> who finally handed the [[Queen's Baton]] to [[Charles, Prince of Wales|The Prince of Wales]].<ref name=CBC-Baton>CBC, 2010 Commonwealth Games, Opening Ceremonies, airdate 3 October 2010, 9:00am-12:30pm (Eastern), circa 2h20m mark, CBC Television main network</ref><ref>Sify Sports, [http://sify.com/sports/india-begins-medal-chase-after-cwg-opening-ceremony-news-news-kkemkfgghej.html \"India begins medal chase after CWG opening ceremony\"], '''ANI''', ''4 October 2010'' . Retrieved 5 October 2010.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{External media\n|width=500px\n|video1= [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JuUR8lR50Yk&t=12146s Opening Ceremony \u2013 Delhi 2010 Commonwealth Games] \n|image1= [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/picturegalleries/8039853/Commonwealth-Games-opening-ceremony-in-pics.html Delhi 2010 Commonwealth Games opening ceremony in pictures, The Telegraph Newspaper]\n|image2= [https://www.theguardian.com/sport/gallery/2010/oct/03/commonwealth-games-opening-ceremony Delhi 2010 Commonwealth Games opening ceremony in pictures, ''The Guardian'' newspaper]\n}}\n* [http://d2010.thecgf.com/gallery/dcwg/opening_ceremony_delhi_2010 Opening ceremony images] at the official [http://d2010.thecgf.com/ site]\n\n{{Commonwealth Games ceremonies}}\n{{Portal bar|Sports|India}}\n\n[[Category:2010 Commonwealth Games|Opening Ceremony]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games opening ceremonies]]\n[[Category:Ceremonies in India]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed cite error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Commonwealth_Games_opening_ceremony"}
